My 2 cents is that it&#39;s MUCH easier to shoot down an idea as being useless than it is to prove that it may have some merit.
It&#39;s just less work to be a know-it-all that debunks everything, than it is to actually prove the vearcity of some phenomenon.
They all laughed at Chris Columbus!!!!!!!!!!!!
Copernicus
Galileo
Einstein
etc. etc. etc.
A lot of people with great ideas were chortled at in their lifetimes.
No amount of proof will EVER convince someone who firmly believes, or doesn&#39;t believe, in something.

